  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "DTC Explanation: P0234"
    },
    {
      "type": "dtc",
      "code": "P0234",
      "text": "DTC P0234: Excess turbocharger boost pressure"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Detection principle explanation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "29_3.0_jpn_11259988_2.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "29_3.0_jpn_11033533_4.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The turbocharger system has its boost pressure controlled by the PGM-FI ECU. If boost pressure rises abnormally, the PGM-FI ECU cuts fuel and controls throttle opening to protect the engine. If the boost pressure remains above the specified pressure for more than the specified time, the PGM-FI ECU judges it as a failure and stores DTC."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Detection frequency, detection sequence, detection time required, detection method type, OBD status"
    },
    {
