    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Failure Criteria"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "The lower engine speed limit for determining abnormal high pressure for engine protection."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "rows": [
        [
          {
            "text": "Engine RPM [ Engine RPM]."
          },
          {
            "text": "2,250 rpm or more"
          }
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "When the intake manifold pressure is determined to be abnormally high for engine protection and continues for more than 2 seconds."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "rows": [
        [
          {
            "text": "Engine Intake Air Pressure [Intake pressure sensor]*"
          },
          {
            "text": "214 kPa (1,600 mmHg) or higher"
          }
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Estimated Failure Site"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "West gate valve closure failure"
        },
        {
          "text": "West gate control SOL.V. open sticking"
        },
        {
          "text": "Turbo charger Actuator piping failure (clogging, disconnection)"
        },
        {
          "text": "Disconnection of cord (VCC line) between PGM-FI ECU and intake pressure sensor"
        },
        {
          "text": "Disconnection of cord (PB line) between PGM-FI ECU and intake pressure sensor"
        },
        {
          "text": "PGM-FI ECU internal failure (barometric pressure sensor)"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Reproducibility Testing Methodology"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "Start the engine, run the radiator fan twice, and then warm up the engine for at least 2 minutes at 3,000 rpm with no load."
        },
        {
          "text": "Engine speed [engine rpm] 3,250 rpm or more and throttle opening 41° or more for at least 2 seconds."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "When conducting test drives, the driver must comply with all laws and regulations, observe good manners, and drive in accordance with the surrounding conditions."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "None."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Store and clear DTC"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If the vehicle is determined to have a fault, a temporary DTC is stored in the PGM-FI ECU memory. If the same failure is detected at the next D/C (two consecutive detections), the PGM-FI warning light comes on and the DTC and freeze data are stored."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If the vehicle is diagnosed and determined to be normal after running consecutive 3D/C runs, the PGM-FI warning light will turn off. In addition, the PGM-FI warning light, temporary DTC, DTC and freeze data are cleared by using the clear command of the scan tool (including HDS) or by removing the 12V battery terminal."
    }
  ],
